// Config.local.xcconfig.example — template for per-developer signing.
//
// Copy this file to Config.local.xcconfig (which is gitignored) and
// uncomment the DEVELOPMENT_TEAM line below, replacing ABCDE12345 with
// your own 10-character Apple Developer team ID.
//
// How to find your team ID:
//   1. Open https://developer.apple.com/account
//   2. Click "Membership" in the left sidebar.
//   3. Copy the value labelled "Team ID" (10 chars, e.g. "ABCDE12345").
//
// Then run:
//   cp Config.local.xcconfig.example Config.local.xcconfig
//   # edit Config.local.xcconfig and set DEVELOPMENT_TEAM
//   xcodegen generate
//   open Maraithon.xcodeproj
//
// CODE_SIGN_STYLE stays Automatic (set in project.yml); Xcode will pick
// up your team ID from here and auto-manage signing certificates.

// DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = ABCDE12345

// Sparkle EdDSA public key for verifying companion app updates.
// Generated once by `./scripts/sparkle_keys.sh`, which prints a
// 44-character base64 string you paste below. The matching private
// key lives in your login Keychain and never leaves your laptop.
// See docs/RELEASE.md > "Generate the Sparkle EdDSA key pair".

// SUPublicEDKey = paste44characterbase64stringfromsparklekeyshereeeee=
